    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-12-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="133"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                <head>133. Memorandum From the <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                    Director of the International Cooperation Administration (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HJB1" type="to">Hollister</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d133fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                        746E.00/12–2355. Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_DAW1"
                            >Dulles</persName>. Copies were forwarded to <gloss target="#t_NEA1"
                            >NEA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_U1">U</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_C1"
                            >C</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_SP1">S/P</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_G1"
                            >G</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_E1">E</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_UMSA1"
                            >U/MSA</gloss>, and <gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-12-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 23, 1955.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I continue to be concerned about the Ceylon situation. If we locate the nuclear
                    power station in the Philippines rather than Ceylon (with which I concur), if we
                    give economic aid to India which is theoretically neutralist but benevolent to
                    the Soviet bloc, if we give economic aid to Egypt which has its arms deal with
                    the Soviet bloc, and if we cannot do anything for Ceylon which has been a
                    staunch and helpful ally, then there is, I think, something seriously wrong.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
